ance, so you can focus on patient care."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What features are included in the white-labeled solution?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Your branded platform includes secure video and text consults, patient self-booking, integrated payments, EHR access, prescriptions, care plans, health trackers, patient notifications, multilingual support, and more—everything needed to deliver modern telehealth under your brand."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the white-labeled telemedicine app compliant with healthcare regulations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The platform is fully HIPAA and GDPR compliant, with built-in audit trails, encryption, role-based permissions, and automated backups. Compliance is included by default, so you don't need to invest in costly security expertise."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can startups and hospitals both use the white-label solution?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Absolutely. Startups benefit from fast go-to-market and investor-ready branding, while hospitals and established clinics use it to strengthen their brand identity and expand digital services. Dedicated cloud hosting is also available for enterprise customers."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What's the difference between white-labelling and custom branding?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Basic \"custom branding\" usually means changing colors or logos inside a vendor's app. Our full white-label solution goes much further—your app is published under your developer accounts in Apple and Google stores, your domain and email are used, and all notifications come from your brand."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does this compare to building my own telehealth app from scratch?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Building your own patient portal and app and fully fledged operations system for your healthcare team can take 6–12 months and cost upwards of $200,000—plus ongoing compliance and maint